parameters:
Mage Relm: I'll do a little investigation. There might be
something, so please wait, everyone.

Thief Nora: That's right! Even before coming here, things
felt strange!

Priestess Sophia: I have this strange sensation as if I'm
being drawn towards something, as if someone is calling
me... It's a weird feeling, isn't it?

Mage Relm: It feels like an ordinary shrine, but there's no
doubt that it's related to Namdo from the magic circle.

Mage Relm: The outfit that Sophia-san is wearing was made to
honor the demon Namdo.

Mage Relm: There might be something that happens when you
wear it... I don't recommend it though.

Mage Relm: There is a possibility that something dangerous
might happen, so Pario-san's [seal] might be the correct
one!

Priestess Sophia: If Pario-san's request is to destroy the
gem, I will try everything I can.

Clea: Understood. If there's anything, I'll do my best to
handle it.
Do you touch the shrine of the demon Namudo?
Priestess Sophia: I will need a little time to prepare.

Priestess Sophia (If I don't wear the attire of the demon
Namudo...)
Priestess Sophia: It wouldn't make sense if it's not me.
Cleric Sophia: Nothing in particular is happening, it seems.
Thief Nora: Don't we need the jewel as well?
Mage Relm: Hey, acting recklessly is dangerous, you know!
Clea: Most likely... Sophia-san will attack!

Thief Nora: Sophia-san...! It's because of me doing
something unnecessary!

Mage Relm: Oh, please calm down! Um, in situations like
this, you should rely on the cleric!

Mage Relm: Hey, Clea-san! Why are you still holding your
weapon up!?

Clea: I don't know what will happen, but it seems like
Sophia-san will wake up.

Cleric Sophia: I will bury all of you for the sake of Demon
Lord Namudo!

Cleric Sophia: Th-This is a j-joke! L-Look, even in a time
like this, *gulp* I can still drink wine!
Clea: So you're the real Sophia-san.
Thief Nora: Yes! There's no mistake!

Mage Relm: Geez... Please stop with these heart-stopping
jokes!

Cleric Sophia: Hehehe, I'm sorry. That gem was sealed with
the grudges of the followers of Namudo.

Cleric Sophia: I clearly heard the voice of hatred denying
our faith.

Cleric Sophia: Not only did it disappear, but the gem also
shattered and vanished like sand.

Clea: The request is complete, let's go report to Pario-
san.

Cleric Sophia (The enchanting demon Namudo... If I can
freely manipulate this power, even that person's heart...)

Cleric Sophia (Hehe, if I do something like that, Clea-chan
and the others will get angry at me, won't they?)

Cleric Sophia: From now on, I will increase the followers of
Lord Namudo.
Cleric Sophia: First, shall we head to the nearby village?

Cleric Sophia: But that's after we take care of them, you
know...
